simpleRenamer v2.0 - Reimplemented in Vala

Written by Karsten-Kai König

Description

This is a simple console-based renamer tool written in Vala. The original
project was written in Python.

Requirements

The requirements are Vala (tested with v0.10) and Gee.

Install

Type in the root directory:

$ make
$ make install

Now you can start the program with 'simpleRenamer'.

Usage

simpleRenamer [OPTION...] <DIRECTORY>

Help Options:
  -h, --help            Show help options

Application Options:
  --pre=PREFIX          set prefix that will be placed to the left of the number
  --post=POSTFIX        set postfix that will be placed to the left of the number
  -l, --list=LIST       use a list of files instead of all files in the directory
  -i, --interactive     choose which files should be renamed interactive
  -c, --conserve        conserve file extension
  -s, --start=START     set startnumber

